## KEY LEARNINGS THIS SESSION

### 1. Idle Scramble is ESSENTIAL (not destructive)
v526 (no idle scramble) = 12.77 vs v519 = 13.99. Removing idle scramble
loses 1.22 points despite both teams sharing cooperative scores.
Junction recycling (scramble → re-align) creates more alignment events.

### 2. Self-play Correlation is NEAR ZERO
TV166 (no idle) had BEST self-play (2.13 avg, consistent) but WORST
tournament (12.77). TV160 (baseline) had WORSE self-play (1.76 avg,
high variance) but BEST tournament (13.99). Self-play results are
MISLEADING for strategy decisions.

